HEADWORD: Suprastapedial
<hw>Su`pra*sta*pe"di*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, that part of
the columella of the ear which projects above the connection with the
stapes, as in many animals.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The
suprastapedial part of the columella.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suprasternal</ent>⟦br⟧
